item.description:
1) There are in society certain mecanisms for circulation (circuits);
2) These circuits clearly reflect the ideology of the producer, but at the same time it is possible they could receive insertions while they circulate;
3) This always happen whenever someone starts it.
Cildo Meireles, 1970.
 &ldquo;Insertions into Mediatic Circuits&rdquo; were a series of short media interventions (insertions) where social networks&rsquo; live video streams were copied, modified, and finally streamed back to social networks in realtime, while the original live stream still occurred.

I&rsquo;ve worked in many other new media projects that are not presented in the main page. Some of these projects are listed here:
 Beberibe (2014), with multiple collaborators;
 Natal Presente de Luz (2013), with Mozart Santos and Simone Mendes;
 Livro dos Softwares Inúteis (2012);
 Mundo ao Redor (2012), with Adriana Carneiro, Ricardo Brazileiro, and others;
 Eita, Porra! (2010), with multiple collaborators;
 Projeto Soma (2009), with Marco Bonachela, Hugo Coutinho, e Henrique Lima;
